nexml.meta:
I noticed while I was proofreading the matrix that two small changes were made to the matrix in pencil: character 139 for the ancestor taxa was circled and was changed from b to a and characters 144 and 145 for taxa Cyprinella garmini were circled and changed from a to c and c to a, respectively. Paula Mabee said to use the penciled changes, which are presumably Richard Mayden's corrections. Alyssa Block 10 July 2009
Unable to access a PDF of the matrix or the original Mesquite file (neither on the webdav). Unsure if there are polymorphic characters. AB 10/17/12
